---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="K-Aesthetica is a K-beauty journal written by people who actually use the products — honest reviews, routine breakdowns, and the science behind glass skin.">
  <div class="wrap">
    <article class="page">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Skincare, minus the hype.</h1>
      <p class="standfirst">K-Aesthetica is a K-beauty journal for people who want the honest version — what actually works, what's just pretty packaging, and the small daily rituals that quietly add up.</p>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>The Korean beauty world is gorgeous, generous, and absolutely flooded with marketing. Ten-step routines, miracle essences, the snail of the month. Some of it is genuinely brilliant. A lot of it is a sticker on a jar. We're here to tell the difference.</p>

        <h2>What we believe</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Barrier first.</strong> A calm, intact skin barrier beats any trending active. Most "bad skin days" are barrier days.</li>
          <li><strong>Fewer, better steps.</strong> A routine you'll actually keep at four steps beats a perfect ten you'll abandon by Thursday.</li>
          <li><strong>Sunscreen is the whole routine.</strong> Everything else is a bonus.</li>
          <li><strong>No miracle claims.</strong> Skincare is maintenance, not magic. We talk in weeks and months, not "overnight."</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we review</h2>
        <p>We use products for at least <strong>four weeks</strong> before forming a verdict, on real skin in real life — not a single-use first impression. We note texture, who a product suits, who should skip it, and the things the brand won't tell you. We don't take payment for positive reviews, and any affiliate or gifted relationship is disclosed in the post.</p>

        <blockquote>Good skincare is boring, consistent, and kind to your barrier. That's the whole secret.</blockquote>

        <h2>A note on honesty</h2>
        <p>Everyone's skin is different. What sent our barrier into its best month might not suit yours — and nothing here is medical advice. Patch test new products, introduce actives slowly, and see a dermatologist for anything persistent or painful.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <Newsletter />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
